 of the License, or (at your option) any later version.

 PLAYSAFE policy flavor — the Google-Play-compliant subset. Google reviews the MERGED manifest, so
 a runtime BuildConfig flag is NOT enough: the Play-restricted permissions + components must be
 physically ABSENT here (their code paths are additionally gated by BuildConfig.POLICY_OPEN so the
 build doesn't reach them). Removed:
  - USE_EXACT_ALARM / SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM — restricted to clock/calendar apps; the node's watchdog
    falls back to inexact alarms automatically (RelaisWatchdog catches the SecurityException), so the
    RelaisWatchdogReceiver itself stays and the node still self-revives.
  - REQUEST_IGNORE_BATTERY_OPTIMIZATIONS — restricted allowlist; the direct-request button is hidden
    in playsafe (the user can still exempt the app manually via system Settings).
  - READ_CALENDAR — calendar-data policy; the read-calendar-events agent skill's handler is gated off.
  - BIND_NOTIFICATION_LISTENER_SERVICE listener + its control activity (notification-access feature).
 (Image generation rides the full flavor only and the endpoint is an honest 501, so there is no
 :imagegen service in any playsafe-eligible variant to remove here.)
-->
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools">

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.USE_EXACT_ALARM" tools:node="remove" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM" tools:node="remove" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.REQUEST_IGNORE_BATTERY_OPTIMIZATIONS" tools:node="remove" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_CALENDAR" tools:node="remove" />

    <application>
        <service android:name="cc.grepon.relais.triage.RelaisNotificationListenerService" tools:node="remove" />
        <activity android:name="cc.grepon.relais.triage.TriageControlActivity" tools:node="remove" />
    </application>

</manifest>
